        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(hooks): expose inbound reply metadata before dispatch",
        "body": "Fixes #88521.\n\n## Summary\n\n- Carry `replyToId`, `replyToBody`, and `replyToSender` from finalized inbound context into canonical hook context and plugin message contexts.\n- Expose those fields through `before_dispatch` event/context types.\n- Add docs for the new first-class reply metadata fields.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed: Discord reply metadata was finalized into inbound context fields, but plugin `before_dispatch` hooks could not see the replied-to message id/body/sender and therefore could not implement reply-aware commands through the public hook API.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout at `/Users/andy/openclaw-88521`, branch `fix/discord-reply-hook-context-88521`, commit `d58abce0b7`.\n\nExact steps or command run after the patch:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/hooks/message-hook-mappers.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts\nnode --import tsx --input-type=module <redacted-hook-mapper-proof>\ngit log --format='%h %an <%ae> %s' upstream/main..HEAD\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```text\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  14 passed (14)\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  188 passed (188)\n[test] passed 2 Vitest shards in 11.28s\n\n{\n  \"canonical\": {\n    \"replyToId\": \"quoted-message-redacted\",\n    \"replyToBody\": \"quoted body redacted\",\n    \"replyToSender\": \"quoted-sender-redacted\"\n  },\n  \"beforeDispatchContext\": {\n    \"replyToId\": \"quoted-message-redacted\",\n    \"replyToBody\": \"quoted body redacted\",\n    \"replyToSender\": \"quoted-sender-redacted\"\n  }\n}\n\ne5be0440cc Andy Ye <35905412+TurboTheTurtle@users.noreply.github.com> Expose reply metadata to before_dispatch hooks\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: A finalized inbound context with `ReplyToId`, `ReplyToBody`, and `ReplyToSender` now reaches the canonical hook context and the plugin-visible `before_dispatch` context as `replyToId`, `replyToBody`, and `replyToSender`.\n\nWhat was not tested: I did not connect to a live Discord gateway; the proof uses a redacted finalized Discord-shaped context through the real hook mapper path and focused dispatch tests.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Maintainer can modify: enabled.\n\n",
